I hate to say it, but the transcript is under automatic copyright (even though it will probably never be enforced). [[c:Commons:Copyright rules by territory/United Kingdom]] says that anonymous works of any kind are copyrighted until 70 years after creation. UK copyright doesn't matter here I guess, but the US copyright is even worse. Because it was published (by 1977 standards) in a foreign country, it will remain under copyright in the US until 95 years later, i.e. January 1, 2073.
